- Word order: Subject-Verb-Object (SVO) or Object-Subject-Verb (OSV)
- Has ergative marking with particle "in"

## Key Grammar Points:
- Ergative marker: "in" (e.g., "Ken in" = "Ken (as subject)")
- Verb stems: Stem I (affirmative), Stem II (dependent/negative)
- Tense markers: "hi" (present), "ta" (past), "ding" (future), "ngei" (perfect)
- Possession: "a" (his/her), "ka" (my), "nang" (your)

